Zambia’s President Says Election to Be Held Sept. 20

-- B y   A n t h o n y   M u k w i t a
-- 
2011-07-28T13:45:21Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-28/zambia-s-president-says-logistical-problems-to-delay-election-to-sept-20.html
(Corrects to remove reference to logistics issues in first
paragraph, election must be held within 90 days of parliament
closing in second.)  Zambia’s President Rupiah Banda said
a national election will take place on Sept. 20.  He spoke on national television today. According to the
Constitution the election should take place within 90 days of
parliament closing, he said. Banda has dissolved parliament.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Anthony Mukwita in Lusaka at 
 amukwita1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net  